The size of the sliding window is `d = k * 2 + 1` (`d` is for diameter). 

We pre-populate the result array `res` with `-1`, and set centered indexes to the sliding window average: ` res[i - d / 2] = sum / d`.

> A catch - we need to store the window sum using a 64-bit integer to avoid overflow.

**C++**
```cpp
vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
    vector<int> res(nums.size(), -1);
    long long sum = 0, d = k * 2 + 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i) {
        sum += nums[i];
        if (i + 1 >= d) {
            if (i >= d)
                sum -= nums[i - d];
            res[i - d / 2] = sum / d;
        }
    }
    return res;
}
```

