# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The code aims to calculate the averages of subarrays of length **2k + 1** within the given vector **nums**. It uses the prefix sum technique to efficiently calculate the cumulative sums of elements in **nums**.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. If k is equal to zero, there are no subarrays to calculate averages for, so the function returns the original vector nums.
2. Initialize variables n (size of nums) and ans (resultant vector) with appropriate values. The ans vector is initialized with -1 as a placeholder value.
3. If k is greater than n/2, it means there are not enough elements to form a subarray of length 2k + 1. In this case, the function returns the initialized ans vector.
4. Create a prefix sum array called prefix to store the cumulative sums of elements in nums. Iterate over the indices of nums, starting from 1, and calculate each element in the prefix array by adding the current element in nums to the previous prefix sum.
5. Set the divisor variable to 2k + 1, which represents the length of the subarray.
6. Initialize the sum variable to 0. It will keep track of the sum of elements within each subarray.
7. Iterate over the range k to n - k - 1 (inclusive) to calculate the averages. For each iteration:
- Calculate the average of the subarray using the formula (prefix[i + k] - sum) / divisor.
- Update the ans vector with the calculated average at index i.
- Update the sum by subtracting the element that is k positions behind the current index, nums[i - k], from the previous sum.
8. After the loop completes, the function returns the ans vector containing the averages of the subarrays.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        if(k==0) return nums;

        int n=nums.size();
        vector<int> ans(n,-1);

        if(k>n/2) return ans;

        //prefix sum
        vector<long long> prefix(n,0);
        prefix[0]=nums[0];

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++) prefix[i]=prefix[i-1]+nums[i];

        int divisor=2*k+1;
        long sum=0;
        for(int i=k;i<n-k;i++){
            ans[i]=(prefix[i+k]-sum)/divisor;
            sum+=nums[i-k];
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

