# Intuition
###### Maintain a window of size (2*k+1). Slide it from left to right and change the window sum accordingly.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- If k==0,the answer corresponds to the value of nums itself.
- If the window size is greater than input size, then the result is all -1 because we can't fit a window in that input.
- In order to address cases where a radius/window cannot be established at the initial indices, the result vector is populated with k instances of -1.
- The sum of the window size is maintained, and upon division by the window size, the value is appended to the result vector.
- At every iteration next number is added and previous number is removed from the sum of window size variable.
- Finally, k instances of -1 are again appended to the result vector.(because window can't be made).

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ --> 

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    void fill_neg_ones(vector<int> &result, int k)
    {
        for(int i = 0;i<k;i++)
        {
            result.push_back(-1);
        }

        return;
    }
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k)
    {

        if(k==0)
        {
            return nums;
        }


        int window_size = 2*k + 1;

        if(nums.size()<window_size)
        {
            vector<int> result(nums.size(),-1);
            return result;
        }


        long long int rad_sum = 0;
        vector<int> result;

        fill_neg_ones(result,k);

        for(int i = 0;i<window_size;i++)
        {
            rad_sum+=nums[i];
        }

        result.push_back(rad_sum/window_size);

        int remove_index = 0;
        int add_index = window_size;

        while(add_index<nums.size())
        {
            rad_sum = (rad_sum - nums[remove_index++] + nums[add_index++]);
            result.push_back(rad_sum/(window_size));
        }

        fill_neg_ones(result,k);
        return result;

    }
};
```

