* Here window size = radius
* The first k and last k value will be -1
* The sum of window ith is ```pre[i+k+1] - pre[i-k]```
**Solution 1: Prefix Array + Sliding Window**
```
class Solution {
    public int[] getAverages(int[] nums, int k) {
        int n=nums.length, radius = 2*k+1;
        long pre[] = new long[n+1]; // use long because integer overflow
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            pre[i+1] = pre[i] + nums[i];
        }

        int res[] = new int[n];
        Arrays.fill(res, -1);
        for(int i=k; i<n-k; i++){
            res[i] = (int) ((pre[i+k+1] - pre[i-k]) / radius);
        }
        return res;
