# Intuition and Approach
This question is a little bit tricky if we go with Prefix and Suffix Sum Approach
But Worry not I will make it Understandable for you my *nakama*,

Okay first understand the prefix sum and suffix sum,
i.e. 
```
array=[1,2,3]
prefix sum array will be = [1,3,6] -> [1, 1+2, 1+2+3] : adding in forward order
suffix sum array will be = [6,5,3] -> [1+2+3, 2+3, 3] : adding in reverse order
```
*(You can refer code now and see how I implemented it)*
If you didn't Understand above example then you can refer youtube to know the concept of prefix sum and suffix sum.

There are Three main cases to before we starting to make our answer vector
(i) if(k==0) -> then we dont need to prefix and suffix sum using this in the start of the code will result in fast code execution
k = no. of element from one side to take
so 2*k -> elements from both left and right
and `2*k+1` -> above + the element self
ps. thats how we take average `elements sum/no. of element` 

(ii) if(k>n/2) -> then we dont have sufficient elements to take from both left and right side at any position of the vector

(iii) this include four different cases for which you can refer code


# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<long long> pre,suf; //use long long as constraints are given
        vector<int> ans;
        long long temp=0,n=nums.size();

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            pre.emplace_back(nums[i]+temp);
            temp+=nums[i];
        }
        temp=0;
        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--){
            suf.emplace_back(nums[i]+temp);
            temp+=nums[i];        
        }
        reverse(suf.begin(),suf.end());
        //reversing the array would help to get the suffix array as.. 
        //..we are inserting the element from start

        //Uncommenting below will help you see the prefix and suffix vector
        // for(auto val:pre){
        //     cout<<val<<" ";
        // }
        // cout<<"\n";
        // for(auto val:suf){
        //     cout<<val<<" ";
        // }
        // cout<<"\n";

        //three cases
        if(k==0){
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                int a;
                a = nums[i];
                ans.emplace_back(a/(2*k+1));                
            }            
        }            
        else if(k>n/2){
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                ans.emplace_back(-1);
            }
        }
        else{
            for(int i=0;i<n-k;i++){
                if(i<k){
                    ans.emplace_back(-1);
                }
                else{
                    long long a;
                    if(i-k == 0 and i+k == n-1){
                        a = pre[i-1] + suf[i+1] + nums[i];
                    }
                    else if(i-k == 0 ){
                        a = pre[i-1] + suf[i+1]-suf[i+k+1] + nums[i];
                    }
                    else if(i+k == n-1){
                        a = pre[i-1]-pre[i-k-1] + suf[i+1] + nums[i];
                    }
                    else{
                        a = (pre[i-1]-pre[i-k-1]) + (suf[i+1]-suf[i+k+1]) + nums[i];
                    }
                    ans.emplace_back(a/(2*k+1));
                }
            }
            for(int i=n-k;i<n;i++){
                ans.emplace_back(-1);
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
