# Intuition
- Keep a fixed-length sliding window of length 2*k+1.
- Slide it from left to right, and update the sum and avg of window.

# Approach
- Take a windows size of window = 2*k+1
- Push nums[i] into the window i.e. windowSum += A[i]
- Pop nums[i-window] out of the window i.e. windowSum -= nums[i-window]
- Assign the average value i.e. ans[i - k] = windowSum/window.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(n)`

- Space complexity: `O(1)`

# Code
```
class Solution{
public:
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k){
        long window = 2*k+1;
        long n = nums.size();
        vector<int> ans(n, -1);

        // edge case
        if(n < window)
            return ans;

        long windowSum = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            windowSum += nums[i];
            if(i-window >= 0)
                windowSum -= nums[i-window];
            if(i >= window-1)
                ans[i-k] = windowSum/window;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

