**Prefix Sum**
```

class Solution {
  public int[] getAverages(int[] nums, int k) {
    long prefix[] = new long[nums.length];
    int ans[] = new int[nums.length];

    long pre = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
      pre = pre + nums[i];
      prefix[i] = pre;
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
      if (i - k < 0 || i + k >= nums.length) {
        ans[i] = -1;
        continue;
      }

      if (i - k - 1 < 0) {
        ans[i] += prefix[i + k] / (2 * k + 1);
        continue;
      }

      ans[i] += (prefix[i + k] - prefix[i - k - 1]) / (2 * k + 1);
    }

    return ans;
  }
}
```

**Sliding Window**

```
class Solution {
  public int[] getAverages(int[] nums, int k) {
int ans[] = new int[nums.length];
Arrays.fill(ans, -1);
int i = 0, j = 0;
long sum = 0;
while (j < nums.length) {
  sum += nums[j];
  if (j - i + 1 < 2 * k + 1) { //window size not yet hit
    j++;
  } else if (j - i + 1 == 2 * k + 1) { // window size hit
    ans[j - k] = (int) (sum / (2 * k + 1));

    sum -= nums[i];
    i++;

    j++;
  }
}
return ans;
}
}
```

