# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Since we have to calculate the avg of a particular window size say ****2*k+1*** , its better to store the summation of the elements upto the index in a preix array. This will avoid from looping to find the sum of the window size.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
First we store the prefix sum in a vector.
```
vector<long long> preSum;
        long long sum=0;
        for(int x:nums){
            sum+=x;
            preSum.push_back(sum);
        }

```

---

After this step the prefix sum is going to look like this
```
/*  
    index -> 0   1   2   3   4   5   6   7   8 
    nums  -> 7   4   3   9   1   8   5   2   6
    preSum-> 7   11  14  23  24  32  37  39  45
*/
```
*So how does it helps to calculate the avg?*

***--->Example 1 :*** Suppose you're at **index->4** **[k=3]**
```
    index -> 0   1   2   3   4   5   6   7   8 
    nums  -> 7   4   3   9   1   8   5   2   6
                 <---------- ^ ---------->
                 |     *Window Size*     |
                low                     high
                 |                       |
    preSum-> 7   11  14  23  24  32  37  39  45
```
By Common observation we know that ,
            ***Window Size =*** 2*k + 1
***Low index =*** i - k
***High index =*** i + k

---

***Window Size sum =*** ```preSum[high] - preSum[low-1]```
```
    index        -> 0   1   2   3   4   5   6   7   8 
    nums         -> 7   4   3   9   1   8   5   2   6
                        <---------- ^ ---------->
                        |   *Window Size Sum*   |
                       low                     high

*Window Size Sum*->  4+3+9+1+8+5+2 = 32 = preSum[high]-preSum[low-1]  
```

---

**Edge case :** While being at index i = k **[k=3]**
```
    index -> 0   1   2   3   4   5   6   7   8 
    nums  -> 7   4   3   9   1   8   5   2   6
             <---------- ^ ---------->
             |     *Window Size*     |
            low                     high
             |                       |
    preSum-> 7   11  14  23  24  32  37  39  45
```
Here ```low = 0``` so ```low - 1 = -1``` which is not possible so
***Window Size sum =*** ``` preSum[high] ```
# Time Complexity
$$O(n) $$  -> Making of preSum
$$O(n) $$  -> Modification of nums

All the Arithmetic and Conditional operations occurs in $$O(1)$$

So ***Total Time Complexity :*** $$2O(n)$$ ≈ $$O(n)$$
# Space Complexity
$$O(n) $$  -> Making of preSum
So ***Total Time Complexity :*** $$O(n)$$ 
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n=nums.size();
        // making the prefix sum array; 
        vector<long long> preSum;
        long long sum=0;
        for(int x:nums){
            sum+=x;
            preSum.push_back(sum);
        }
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            //if the index is out of bounds for the window size [i.e for index->i , window size->{i-k,i+k} ] we set nums[i]= -1.
            if(i<k || n-1-i<k){
                nums[i]=-1;
            }
            else{

            int low = i-k , high = i+k;
            if(low-1<0){ // handling the edge case
                    nums[i] = preSum[high]/(2*k+1);
                }
            else{
                    nums[i] = (preSum[high]-preSum[low-1])/(2*k+1);
                }
            }

        }
        return nums;
    }
};
```

