# Intuition
    The problem requires calculating the moving average of an array
     nums with a given window size 2k+1.
     We need to find an efficient solution to compute the average
     efficiently for each window.
# Approach
    To solve this problem efficiently, we can use the concept of 
    incremental calculation. Instead of recalculating the sum of each 
    window from scratch, we can update the sum by subtracting the element

    going out of the window and adding the new element coming into the window.


    Create an array avg to store the averages for each window.
    Check for the edge case where k is 0. In this case, return the 
    original array nums.
    Initialize the sum variable as the sum of the first k elements of
    nums.

    Iterate through the array nums from index k to nums.Length - 1:
    If the current index is less than k or greater than nums.Length -
    k - 1, set avg[i] to -1 since the window is not complete.

    Otherwise, update the sum by subtracting the element going out of
    the window (i.e., nums[i - k]) and adding the new element coming 
    into the window (i.e., nums[i]).

    Compute the average by dividing the sum by k.

    Set avg[i] to the computed average.

    Return the avg array.

# Complexity
    Time complexity: O(n), where n is the length of the input array
     nums. We iterate through the array once to compute the averages.
    Space complexity: O(n), where n is the length of the input array
     nums. We use an additional array avg to store the computed averages.
# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int[] GetAverages(int[] nums, int k) {
        int[] avg = new int[nums.Length];
        if (k == 0)
            return nums;

        long sum = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.Length; i++) {
            if (i < k || i > nums.Length - k - 1 || k == 0) {
                avg[i] = -1;
            } else {
                if (i == k) {
                    for (int j = 0; j <= 2 * k; j++) {
                        sum += nums[j];
                    }
                } else {
                    sum -= nums[i - k - 1];
                    sum += nums[i + k];
                }
                avg[i] = (int)(sum / (2 * k + 1));
            }
        }

        return avg;
    }
}

```

