# Approach
The window's size is defined as 2*k + 1, where k is the radius. Our goal is to compute the answer for indices ranging from k to n-k since only those indices possess k elements on both their left and right sides. This computation can be easily achieved by using a prefix array.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    #define ll long long
public:
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<ll> px(n);
        px[0] = nums[0];
        for(int i=1 ; i<n ; ++i) {
            px[i] = px[i-1] + nums[i];
        }

        vector<int> ans(n,-1);
        int d = 2*k + 1;
        for(int i = k ; i<n-k ; ++i) {
           ans[i] = (px[i+k] - (i-k > 0 ? px[i-k-1] : 0))/ d;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

