Sliding Window

# Approach
1)Traverse the first k element make it as -1 and store their sum.
2)For next k+1 elements store the sum and when i==2*k put the sum/(2*k+1) in ans[k].
3)For elements from 2*k+1 till n-k add current element and delete curr-(2*k+1) element, store the sum/(2*k+1) in ans[i-k].
4)Traverse last n-k elements and store -1 in them. 

