# Intuition

Try to find sum for ith index with help of sum calculted for (i-1)th index.

# Approach

Start with a pointer at index 0 and a start index for starting value of element for 
numbers inside radius k,Now for starting and last k element average will be -1 and for 
remaining elements in between them, first find the average for kth element and next
time to find sum inside the circle delete last element from sum i.e at index start and add the number at index start+2*k+1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> getAverages(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> ans(n,0);
        int start=0,end = 0;
        long long sum=0;
        while(end<n){
            if(end<k || end>n-k-1){ans[end]=-1;}
            else if(end==k) {
               for(int i=0;i<2*k+1;i++){
                   sum+=nums[i];
               }
               start=0;
               ans[end] = sum/(2*k+1);
            }
            else{
                sum = sum-nums[start]+nums[start+2*k+1];
                ans[end] = sum/(2*k+1);
                start++;
            }
            end++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

